HEADWORD: Pupipara
<hw>Pu*pip"a*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Pupiparous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of
Diptera in which the young are born in a stage like the pupa. It
includes the sheep tick, horse tick, and other parasites. Called also
<altname>Homaloptera</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pupiparous</ent>⟦br⟧
